{
  "text": "On the basis of HRCT it was impossible to subclassify patients with LONIPCs (BO, interstitial pneumonia, DAD, BOOP). None of the patients fulfilled the clinical and CT definitions for BO. Three of four patients with GVHD had bullae (Fig. 2 ) and unilateral pneumothorax (Fig. 2) . However, patients with GVHD did not show a specific pattern of abnormalities on HRCT (Table 2 ). In the patient with DAD, the pattern on HRCT, severe GVHD and poor clinical outcome are in accordance with reports in the literature [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In this patient the lung abnormalities were extensive (Fig. 3) . Two patients were classified as having BOOP on the basis of clinical and CT findings; lung parenchyma involvement was extensive (Fig. 4) . In the two patients who had allogeneic BMT and mild GVHD, the clinical course was satisfactory (Fig. 5) .",
